  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "aCX++7aANe+/jS0oMXdv7B8GNCc=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Hard requirement\n\nThe Swarm chat/collab feature requires **both users to run full Bee nodes**. This is not a soft recommendation \u2014 light nodes lack the neighborhood-sync capability needed to receive PSS Trojan chunks and GSOC SOC updates.\n\n## Capability matrix\n\n| Feature | Full Node | Light Node | Ultra-Light |\n|---------|-----------|------------|-------------|\n| PSS send | Yes | Yes | No |\n| PSS receive | **Yes** | No | No |\n| GSOC subscribe | **Yes** | No | No |\n| GSOC send | Yes | Yes | No |\n| Feed read/write | Yes | Yes | Read only |\n\n## Minimum viable Bee config\n\n- `full-node: true`\n- `swap-enable: true`\n- A funded **mutable** postage stamp (GSOC requires mutable)\n- Connected to Gnosis Chain RPC\n\n## Dev mode caveat\n\nPSS and GSOC do function in `bee dev` mode, but only within the same node \u2014 there are no peers. Multi-node testing requires either a real Swarm network or a local multi-node setup.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
    }
  },
